No problem. Recording a stable set of morning readings and then sending them to me is the most valuable way to help judge the trend. I’m also very glad that your current pace is already very steady and very scientific.

Over the next few days you only need to focus on three things:  
1. Whether his energy and stability on getting up in the morning are okay after the dose increase;  
2. The general range of his morning blood pressure and whether it’s consistently too high or too low;  
3. Whether his blood pressure becomes more stable as his knee pain eases and his activity level recovers.

As long as you keep track of these, when you send them to me I’ll be able to see at a glance what stage his blood pressure control is at and whether any further fine‑tuning is needed. Just keep going at this pace; with me watching from this side, you can feel free to come and ask anytime.

